verbose_text: Oestradiol participation in the aetiology of depressive disorders may be associated not only with the regulation of tryptophan hydroxylase 2 but also with the expression of monoamine oxidase A and B, serotonin transporter, and serotonin-1A receptor.
evidence: expression of monoamine oxidase A and B, serotonin transporter, and serotonin-1A receptor
